values:
Today I am moving out of my dorm and back home. I'm chomping at the bits for my mum and step-dad to get here with boxes. I have mostly everything packed away so there will be little work to be done. I just want out of here and back in my own room. I will be without the net for about a month, or at least until I get to England, so posting here will be scarce or nonexistent. But all the same I will be working during this time. Heaven knows I need the money.

  In other news, since I will be traveling abroad for two months this summer I decided to create a travel blog. I won't be updating it any until I am in England, but I thought I would go ahead and post the link here. :)

mysticbard.wordpress.com/
  I'm still trying to work out a few kinks on it until I am happy with the way it is set up. And I could use a good creative title instead of "The Adventures of  a Pirate". But I am a pirate...I'm going to be boarding Lord Nelson's ship...perhaps I should just stick with that. :D The only downside is I know other people, who don't know the extent of my affiliation with pirates, will be reading it and I am sure they will raise an eyebrow. But who cares. That's me.

  I also decided a Flickr account to host the numerous photos I will be taking so I can share it with others. Granted it will be directly linked to my travel blog I thought I would still provide the website here as well.

www.flickr.com/photos/wayfaringbard/

  Still trying to work out kinks on this site as well. (More like trying to learn how to use it.) Just excuse the one picture I already have posted. I was making sure the silly thing worked.

  Well, that is all for now. I will see the lot of you on the other side of the pond. :)

Maybe I am going crazy. I feel like I am in some sort of psychotic ward and no matter my behavior I am deemed crazy. If I act normal then I am crazy. If I act crazy then I am crazy. No matter the behavior my diagnosis will always be crazy. You can't just be emotional because that makes you unstable.

  I also feel like I am standing in a crowded room, screaming to the top of my lungs and no one is listening. Do these people not see it? What story has she told them? Barely a week ago she was still leading me on to believe she still wanted to fix things and I was stupid enough to believe her. Yet she played me for a fool, has the gall to call me obsessed because I am hurt, and her friends believe she deserves to be happy. How does anyone who causes the same hurt repeatedly in a matter of months deserve to be happy? What right do they have? If she didn't give a damn about what she did to me then why does she deserve to be happy? I want someone to answer that question. I'm the one that deserves to be happy after she ripped my heart out of my chest. I am the one who needs a day where I am not waking up in pain and ending that day in tears.

  Do I have every thing all wrong? Am I seeing things backwards? Am I going insane?

  I wish I could pull the wool away from everyone's eyes and show them what has really been going on. I can guarantee none of her friends knew that she was still talking to me. Most less the things she was telling me, I want to scream and pull my hair out from frustration. Its just more damage, more emotional harm.

  I could hurt her. I still have that letter saved to my computer. Just a couple of clicks would ruin her little happy world. Its not like she can do anything worse to me. Her cruel words of calling me obsessed because I was in love with her are very piercing. She deserves to get her heart ripped out her chest like she did to me. Not including her amount of deceit.

 I hope she gets her heart crushed. Its the least she deserves.

It is like mother says, everyone we meet in our lives we meet for a reason.

   I believe that very much with Mr. Knockemus. After a very disappointing set back concerning college I emailed him with the problem I faced. He called me today to make sure I was okay....it really meant a lot. He told me to check my email so I did. After a discussion on what I needed to do he left me this beautiful poem by William Stafford called "Ask Me".


 
Some time when the river is ice ask me
mistakes I have made. Ask me whether
what I have done is my life. Others
have come in their slow way into
my thought, and some have tried to help
or to hurt: ask me what difference
their strongest love or hate has made.

I will listen to what you say.
You and I can turn and look
at the silent river and wait. We know
the current is there, hidden; and there
are comings and goings from miles away
that hold the stillness exactly before us.
What the river says, that is what I say

This is just to let everyone know I'm still around. *waves*

  Life has been quiet hectic lately.

  I was promoted at work the week before Christmas to finally bear the title of assistant manager. The work hours have been really long. For the past four weeks I have honestly not worked anything under 50 hours a week. Last week had to be the worst because the compressor for our main cooler died and we had to keep the milk in ice all week long.

  My sister is now engaged. Her boyfriend of a year, Greg, proposed to her on New Year's Eve. So, of course, everyone is happy for her. I'm happy for her, but I'm tired of hearing about it.

  Saturday night I went to my first ever NBA game. It was the Charlotte Bobcats vs. the Detroit Pistons. The short story of how I got the tickets was because of a contest at work. Ardra ended up giving the tickets to me because I told her I would try my hardest to go. Luckily, mum took the night off from work and we went. Our tickets were for seating in a suite which was just incredible. It was bascially an open room with a private mini-bar. The game itself was fantastic. For the Bobcats to be a relatively new team they played a hard game against the more aged Pistons. Sadly, they lost by three points. The overall score was Bobcats 101 and Pistons 104. 

  Otherwise, not much has changed. Christmas was nice, but New Year's was awful.

  So to round it all off I thought I would post the story I wrote for Brittany for Christmas......Well, I was. Stupid computers.

There is something in life we cannot avoid and that is making mistakes.


  But the only way we learn anything from them is when we admit we were wrong and realize it was a mistake on our part.

  Even though I swore off ever posting to this journal again I felt like I needed to do this.


  Cindy, I read your entry about us and I feel....bad. Over the past few days it has been really bothering me and this has been before I read your entry. I even mentioned it to Cion that it was. I really do think I made a mistake. I was acting too rashly. So if you read this I am sorry. Currently I want to kick myself for running off on a friend who has helped me through a lot and has been there to listen to me when the going got tough. 

   Of course, along with just reading your entry I just found out your book was not being published till next year. I never said this to anyone, but the Sunday before last I went shopping. My most important visit was to Barnes and Noble, of course, and I remember when I was looking at the new fantasy books I was eagerly looking to see if your title was stuck in there as well. I'm really sorry to hear this. You anticpated it so much.

  So hopefully we can make things better now. (And believe me, dear,  it wasn't over birthdays.) *hugs*

Well, sadly faire season has officially come to an end for me. Pirate weekend was a lot of fun, but really cold. By noon I did not have any feeling in my fingers.

  So....since I was lazy and did not feel like loading all of my faire pictures I simply oicked out a few of my favorites to share here. They are in no particular order so I hope you enjoy!



By an amazing stroke of luck I was able to salvage some of the picture Brittany took of Candice Night and I. She is obviously the lead singer of Blackmore's Night. :P



Wow. My pictures are really small. *kicks computer from denying access to photobucket* Anyways, this is the Chickenman, He is quite hilarious and his garb is amazing right down to his boots.



Its Don Juan and Miguel! I love their facial expressions.



Here is my favorite picture I managed to take of Don Juan. Brittany and I both had the wonderful pleasure of him kissing our hands. :D



Miguel smelling his fingers. Not wanting to reveal where they have been.



Fishes and loaves brought to you by Hey Nunnie Nunnie!



I was forturnate enough to run into a group of rfers at pirate weekend so from left to right we have, as they are known on the forum, a gentleman's name I cannot remember, ladiedragon, Lady Mikalaya, Jeremy, Lady Glorianna, and myself.



Uhh....and this is Scaramouche from the Tortuga Twins. :P



I love this picture! This is Shantyman from Pirate Shantyman and Bonnie Lass.



You cannot have faire without the Tortuga Twins. They gained a fan in Brittany that weekend. Monkeys Rule! *cackles*



And lastly here is one for Brittany. This Zilch the Torysteller and he is perhaps one of the most funniest men you will ever meet. Fighting Buccaneers! *rolls on floor laughing*

It has been a long time posting. I guess we can either say I have been busy or I have been hibernating. However, busy would be more accurate.

  My birthday turned out really pleasant. Thursday night we attended the Blackmore's Night concert and I honestly feel sorry for anyone who missed it. Their music is wonderful on cd's, but seeing them play live is amazing. Sadly, the concert was not sold out, but it was fantastic. The energy of the crowd really influenced the band and Candice Night sung her heart out. She was just amazing. After the concert finally came to an end Candice stayed on stage long enough to sign autographs. I pretty much rushed the stage with Brittany in tow. She was sweet enough to sign our concert tickets. She is very kind and very beautiful. Overall, I will say this. If you are ever lucky enough to have BMN to play near you....GO SEE THEM. You will be saying afterwards they are the best concert you have ever been to. (Even Brittany said they were better than seeing Off Kilter and thats saying something for her. :P)

  The weather for the faire turned out beautiful. I managed to wear my new frock coat with ease only to be harassed by a misinformed misfortune teller. He claimed there were no pirates in the 16th century and that I needed to learn my history better. I plan to gain my revenge on him this weekend. I already have 3 pirates on my list that existed during the 16th century. I also probably spent more money than I should have. I splurged and bought myself one of those wonderful shoulder puppets. Mine is a gryphon and I named him Artemis. Not exactly sure where the name came from, but as soon as he was sat upon my shoulder I felt like that was the name he should be given. Then after that I was inspired to create a whole new faire character. She is going to be a mage practice in the elemental magics and potions. Of course, her little furry friend is the baby gryphon Artemis. So far this new character does not have a name or much of a history, but I'm working on it. 

  So with this new character is two I made a couple more purchases to accompany her. One of them was a really neat staff that was only $22 and then a new short chemise of a gold color to go with my brand spanking new Moresca bodice. (I am in love with the bodice.)

  Day 2 of the faire turned out just as nice, but a bit more chilly. I gave my mage garb its first run and it turned out really nice. Except the wire wrapping on my potion bottles did not hold up as nicely as I hoped. I had to cut off the wire because they were tangled. Oh well. I did try at least.

  Anyways, I am fortunate enough to go back to faire this weekend on Sunday. This weekend at faire is Pirate Weekend and the Pyrates Royale are supposed to perform. I'm rather excited about it. I have been wanting to go to a pirate themed weekend, but could never get the time off. At least the frock coat will come in handy because it is suuposed to be rather cold this weekend.

 On to other news. I have NO idea what to buy my exchange person on the ren forum. He is more of a anime nut than into anything faire based. So this should really be interesting.

 Yesterday I went clothes shopping simply because I needed more jeans. I really hate trying on jeans because I know that every pair I try on is not going to fit me properly. However, I thought I saw some hope when I saw my favorite brand of jeans now doing their sizes in different lengths of short, regular, and long. So I grab the size I wear on both the short and regular to sort of do a comparison...and man were the results shocking. I try on the regular first. They fit just fine, but like usual were somewhat long on me. Then I try on the shorts and regretted it. You would think that since they were the same size of jeans the only difference would be the length. Oh no. These jeans were tighter and shorter than I wanted them. Mom recommended trying on jeans found in the petite section. Even worse mistake. The length was fantastic, but the allowance for the hips was below my hips so it looked like I had bulging thighs. Yes, I have came to the conclusion I will never find a pair of jeans that actually fit me. Argh.

  Now I am just talking about ridiculous things that people would care less about. Ugh.

I wish I could say that I have been doing well, but I haven't. There have been some things happening at work which almost caused me to have an emotional breakdown at work last night. Its quite sad when you come out of the bathroom with swollen eyes and greet Patrice, who surprised me with a visit, with sobs. I haven't seen her since December of last year and I felt terrible that she had to see me in such a state.

  Maybe when I have time I can explain it all, but time is seriously something I am lacking. So to make a long story short I will say that I feel like I am getting abused. Yes, I decided to learn paperwork and the such so Diane could have time off and now I am regretting every minute of it. It seems that now since she has someone else that can do the work she has become greedy. She is going to absolutely see to it that she gets her time off while it is not the same for me. After tomorrow I will only have one day off for the next 15 days.  I'm expected to work the day Brittany comes down for her visit and expected to work the day she leaves. Hell no. the latter is not happening. If Diane doesn't  like it I will just not show up. Its not fair to me to have to give up ALL of my free time for the next two weeks to have my damn time with Brittany cut short.

  My chance to go to opening weekend at CRF was shot to hell because I got called in to work on my day off.

  I'm hoping when I call Moresca today they will have good news about my bodice.

  Has the world abandoned me? I feel like it has. I don't even know why I bother to post here anymore.

  My life is gone. I'm depressed.

 My period keeps coming back every two weeks which is not good. But I don't have health insurance currently despite having to constantly remind Diane I need insurance. So I can't go the doctor.

 I'm tired of having to listen to everyone elses problems, but not having anyone willing to listen to mine.

 What little bit of weight I did manage to gain has disappeared because of my damn job.

 I need to  be working on my college applications, but I don't have time to.

 I'm going to get my hair cut and permed today in attempt to make myself feel better, but nothing can take back the betrayal I have felt at work.

  And everytime I try to go somewhere to cry someone one is either knocking at the door or calling my name. Everyone is always needing something from me.

 And i'm bloody damn sick of it.

I've done it! I finally picked my color!

  I finally picked, with the help of my dear, the burgundy bodice!

  My order has been placed so lets just hope they have it in stock and in the right size. O_o

For the past few days I have been wondering when would be the best time to bring up a semi-exciting change in my life.  One reason I have not mentioned anything since I received the news Tuesday was because I did not want to make Cion feel any worse about herself than she already is. Usually anything that happens good for me she doesn't take very well and it has made me...reluctant. But regardless I don't think there will ever really be a good time to bring it up.

 Tuesday Diane called me. Tuesday I was made Assistant Manager.

  I start my training Monday morning. I have to be there bright and early at 6am. For the first day she just wants me to watch her as she does the paperwork, reports, etc. Luckily, I do have Tuesday off, I was supposed to have Monday off but oh well. For the rest of next week except for the weekend I have to be at work at 4:30 in the morning. Honestly, that is the only part of the job I'm dreading because I am not an early morning person. Fortunately, I wouldn't have to always work in the mornings because once my training is done I will be stuck back on nightshift. The only times I would have to open would be on the days Diane has off. 

  I'm semi-excited. The only person at work that knows I'm AM is Angela whom I told last night. She was happy for me and thought I deserved it. She said she would much rather work under me than Sherra. That gave me a little bit of confidence. I'm hoping that everyone else will feel the same. Its like I told Angela last night, just because I'm AM now does not mean I'm going to change personally. In my opinion you should never let a higher position change your personality and I'm not going to let that happen to me. I'm still going to be Kiera.

  Mom gave me mixed reactions when I told her. At first she did not seem happy at all about it. I had told her as soon as I got off the phone with Diane. After her initial reaction I quietly turned around and went straight back to my room. I think she realized what she did because she came in a few minutes later talking to me about it. After that incident it sort of killed any joy I had about it. Thats kinda the reason why I never said anything to you sooner, dear, I'm sorry. I know we promised to not keep things from each other. But its hard to tell people some things when they will only get jealous, upset, or depressed.

  Otherwise, I stayed up till 3 this morning just to finish reading HMS Surprise. So now I think Maturius Command is next. I think I spelled that right. O_o I have to say the storyline of this book was rather pale in comparison to the first two in the series, but it was still good nonetheless.

I think I found my new best friend...:D

http://damseldress.com/piratecoat.html

The fabrics choices are gorgeous and its such a unique design. Sadly, its a really hefty price tag, but so so gorgeous. Cion had me send her a link and she is going to take a look at it to see if she could figure out a pattern.

 Omg! pretty!

Why do men always assume they can give better directions than women? I can't even begin to count how many times I personally have been asked directions to Myrtle Beach. I will begin on the directions when a man will always jump in and try to give the directions instead. Then when the person who asked for directions leaves some men will have the gall to tell me I was only going to confuse them. Okay, I've been to the beach many many times and I know perfectly well how to get there. I tell them which stoplights to turn at, which landmarks to look for, etc and supposedly my directions are confusing. *snorts*

  However, this leads to last night. A lady came in the store last night and was asking for directions to interstated 77. She was on her way back to Ohio from the beach. I know how to get to 77. Just go north to Rockingham, pick up 74 west, then pick up 77 in Charlotte. I tried telling her that, but she didn't want to go through Charlotte. So I pulled out some maps and tried to find her an alternate route. While doing so this crazy black man came in (someone I can't stand but things I'm supposed to hold conversations with him) asks what we were doing and then butts into the whole situation. I was livid. He gave her the exact same directions I did, but old her that 74 would not take her into Charlotte and the dumb woman believed him! I had just finished telling her the same thing and she refused that route because she said it would take her into Charlotte! I was so incredibly angry. I believe that if I wasn't on the clock I would have had to physically hurt that man. All I can say is the woman is stupid. Having lived in the Monroe, Matthews, Charlotte area till I was 18 I know very damned well that 74 takes you right INTO Charlotte.

  I really just hate men....except for Russell Crowe. XD

  Then I manage to get to the library today and discover I have a flat tire. -_- So I've got to hang out here till my stepdad comes down from work and fixes it. Not that I'm complaining. It will give me extra time here, but still its annoying. I'm always the one getting flat tires.

  I puttered around some this morning with the Ben and Lorelei outline. Even though I never completed the draft I'm already making changes to the original. I'm not so much doing an outline because that is what I plan to go by, but more so because I'm using it as a timeline. There is a bunch, and I truly mean a lot, of story to those two characters so my main reason for an outline is to put my subplots in order. Plus, it gives me a way to jot down those plots I like so I don't forget them. So this can be a positive step in getting my creativity active again.

Even though the temperatures outside still reach 90 degrees, after weeks of have temps in the 100s with a high humidity it feels like a major cool down. Usually during the early hours of morning and the really late hours of night it almost feels like Autumn outside.

  My weekend was pretty uneventful except I did break a record of how many movies I watched in one sitting. Since I had Saturday off and I was going to be home alone I went to Movie Gallery and rented several movies. I bought Proof of Life, but rented Mystery, Alaska and Pan's Labyrinth. Proof of Life and Mystery, Alaska were naturally good. Any Russell Crowe movie usually is. Pan's Labyrinth though...wow. I'm not sure where to begin with that one. First, it is a foreign film so the entire movie is in Spanish and you must read subtitles, but after awhile you get so used to reading that you begin to think you can understand what they are saying. The storyline was incredibly unique. It is difficult to say that this movie reminds me of anything I have seen before. The little girl in the story is really charming and I love her imagination and gift for storytelling. However, I completely forgot that the movie was rated R while watching it so the gore took me by surprise. If this movie were to have a flaw I would say it was the gore. I honestly can't stomach strong violent scenes. I can handle blood, but these were quiet gruesome. But with that aside if you can manage the few places of gore then you will enjoy the movie. I highly recommend it.

  I did finish reading Post Captain so know I am reading HMS Surprise. I'm not plowing through this one like I have the previous two because I've been more in a creative mood than sit and read mood. However, I'm about 150 pages through and am enjoying as much as the others. At least now we have the ship that I am acquainted with so I am some sort of familiar ground. I noticed though that there is a particular character in the first book that has disappeared thus far. Mowett. He wasn't in Post Captain and so far not in HMS Surprise, but there are characters from the first book that have carried through. Pullings, Bonden, Babbington, and Joe Plaice. But I know he comes back eventually. I miss the little snippets of his poetry. :)

  There has been an interesting development at work though. Sherra has turned in her keys and stepped down from her position as assistant manager. I found this to be incredibly amusing. For how long did I have to tolerate her constant arse kissing and lies just to get the job to begin with and now she steps down! If I could have rolled on the floor and laughed I would have, but I didn't fell like providing our customers with entertainment. And Diane might not have approved. So....its possible I may be in the running again for that position (this will be the 4th time now.) However, I'm not going to get my hopes up. I will just work like I usually do and be myself. Nothing more. Of course, I was wondering why Sherra stepped down from the position. According to Ava, who I seem to have as an accomplice, she was at the store when Sherra turned in her keys. A couple of days ago Diane posted noted about not closing the pizza side down till a certain time. (Sherra was notorious for closing up everything as early as 6pm.) So naturally, as was meant, Sherra takes a large offense by there notes and gets really mad. Ava said she was slamming and banging things. But there is the reason she quit the position. Over a damn note that rang true. Of course, I have found at that not many people liked her as assistant manager. She liked to boss people around, but would never do any work herself. Employees will never like that from someone with a position. That I have learned and have felt myself. It always annoyed me when Anita, the former manager, would ask me to do all this stuff , but she would never make an effort to help. She had no idea what went into the upkeep of that store. Sherra, like Anita, was abusing her power. Plus, after I got to thinking about it even before Sherra got AM people didn't like her very well. That can affect your position greatly. It doesn't help to have the resentment of your employees.

  So anyways, it brought a little joy to my week.

  I'm a lucky girl and have the weekend off so I am going to attempt a trip to Monroe to see 3:10 to Yuma. Hopefully, my grandma will tag along. But if not...oh well.

  Of course, my last entry was on choosing a new bodice. If anything were to help I've come up with a color theme. I want my new outift to be in Fall colors. Reds, oranges, yellows, purples, rust colors, etc. I'm still trying to figure out what bodice I want, but since I kinda have my colors in place maybe it won't be so difficult to choose now. As a note: Even though the Moresca bodices carry a hefty price tag they are amazingly made. Brittany and I had a chance to see their booth at GARF this year and these bodices mean serious business. Then again, the cost is still daunting. But I'm incredibly weak for how they can put together color combinations in their bodices with several brocade colors in one. So pretty.

I'm wanting a new bodice. A well made and properly fitting one. Whether I will buy one or not before CRF I'm not sure, its really going to depend on money. But I want one nonetheless and I have my eyes set on a few.

  First, here are the links to the ones I am looking at.

The Goddess Bodice:
http://www.oddbodkin.com/shop/index.php?main_page=product_info&cPath=17_5&products_id=260
(It comes in more than just the bright blue and red. Feel free to browse the colors and vote your opinion.)

The Max Bodice:
http://www.moresca.com/shopping/product_details.php?id=115
(Since there are a million color and pattern choices I haven't decided on a good color for that one yet.)

Finally, the Pirate Bodice:
http://www.moresca.com/shopping/product_details.php?id=309
(If I was to get this one I would get the color combination shown on the bottom left.)

Now, I. going to attempt my first poll....

So much for having three days off. Because one of the ladies a work with has a dying mother I'm stuck putting in more hours. Thats gonna equal 8  hours of over time already on my next paycheck.

  Speaking of jobs. My hunt has thus far been rather unsuccessful. I had called the construction place looking for a receptionist, but they wouldn't take me on account of my lack of knowledge on construction. Bugger. South Carolina has to be one of the worst places to try to find a job. The unemployment rate here is so high so there are a lot of people trying to find jobs. Cheraw is going to be lucky by getting a few new businesses. Since they have built the new super Wal-mart they will be putting in a Lowes, Fatz Cafe, and Zaxbys. And according to my sister yesterday Chesterfield is supposed to be getting a new gas station (like we really need another) and a Bojangles. The Bojangles infuriated me. Cheraw has a Bojangles. Why can't they bring in a restuarant that we don't have yet? Like Chick-fil-a or even better Taco Bell? This is a stupid state quite honestly.
  Howvever, I had to make the decision to stay on at my current job until I got lucky. If I could afford to not work until I could find another then I wouldn't stay, but thats  not how it is. There are bills to pay.

  I had the strangest dream last night that I was back at tech, for what reason I don't know. Of course, most of the people there I didn't know. Mrs. Watson, my old math instructor, walked past me and pretended she didn't know who I was. Feeling somewhat scared I went to Mr. Knockemus's office only to find someone else in there. Someone kinda like me, but wasn't me. I think my stress over getting my applications done is getting to me.

 And why is everyone wanting to be an Irish pirate? Honestly? 

  Finally, got my frock coat worked out. Brittany was so sweet as to buy the fabric for it yesterday. But it is going to be burgundy! I'm gonna be super sexy. XD And I was going to do gold buttons, but I think I have changed my mind to cloth covered. I had reminded myself yesterday that Lorelei's coat is actually rather plain and not flashy. What do you think, dear? And does anyone know how to do functioning pockets? Its not necessary, but my coat will have what looks like pockets, but they don't function and I think real pockets would be very useful. (I'm sure Brittany is going to want to kill me already since I'm making her line my coat even though it doesn't need to be lined. XD)

 Hmm....I'm bored now.

Mice, ants, and spiders. I dealt with them all this weekend.

 I was lucky to have the weekend off from work so I planned to kick back and relax a little, but in reality that never happens. My Saturday began with my kitty Oscar catching a baby mouse in the house. My other kitty Angelo and our little dog Punky watched him rather jealously. For some odd reason I called mom to tell her about the mouse and what Oscar was doing to it and how it died. Rather disgusting I know. With one mouse less in our house I opened my closet door to hang up some clothes when I noticed to my great horror my renaissance garb had become infested with ants. Why they were on my garb I don't know, but I had to get them out of there. So I took my garb out of the closet and hung them outside on the clothes line in hopes the heat would run them off. Thats when I had my second encounter with a mouse.  I was carrying my garb in one hand and once I had got outside I pulled off a hanger that held a bodice. There snuggled in the laces of my bodice was another slightly larger mouse. Before I could scream or panic he dropped away from the laces and darted up a tree. I quickly deposited the garb on the line because they were still covered in ants and I didn't want to get bit. It was back to my closet, now with more caution after the mouse, to finish collecting my garb when I noticed a nice hole in the bottom of my green cloak. It was my birthday present one year from grandma and had cost $50 from faire. After seeing the hole I no longer felt sympathy for the pathetic little mouse that had dangled earlier from Oscar's mouth. With all my garb cleared from my closet it was time to find out where the ants were coming from when I heard mom scream, "Punky caught another mouse!" Who needs mousetraps? I eventually did find the ant source and sprayed the heck out of my closet with ant spray. And fortunately my cloak was the only thing ruined by that little vermin.

  Of course, after all that I was treated to dinner and a movie by my grandma since my sis and mom were working. I also went back to A.C. Moores to back what I would need to make Brittany's book.

 Sunday was less eventful....until that night. I was bored and working on some silly pictures when a spider crawled out from behind a shelf and onto my curtains. I swear it was big enough to eat me and I really really hate spiders. Nearly screaming, I darted from my room (which reminds me of a commercial I've heard on the radio) and begged my stepdad to kill it. He found a cup with a lid and went to get the spider.   Speaking of pirates I had a part of Lorelei's history become clear to me while I toured the pirate exhibit a second time. I have always tried to come up with a way to explain Donal's suicide. (Donal is Lorelei's father.) However, while watching the short documentary at the exhibit I knew. The factual history of the time is Spain ruled the ocean with its Armada and England and France wanted to wip out Spain's naval power. So the British and French hired pirates to do their dirty work. Once the Spanish naval power was no longer supreme, France and England released the pirates from their service. Pirates began to grow in numbers and since they were no longer occupied with the Spanish they began to attack merchant ships. England and France saw this as a problem so they set their forces into wiping out piracy. 
 
  Thus this is what happens to Lorelei's father. Donal actually helped to surpress the Spanish power,but was turned on by the Royal Navy once his work was done. He manages to avoid them for years except for the day he commits suicide. Why does he do it? Because he does not want to give them the pleasure of hanging a man who once helped them. (Even though I don't hate the navy, after that tidbit ti kinda makes me bitter I guess. I am a pirate sympathizer after all. :P)

  But it still doesn't answer why he would abandon his only daughter so quickly. Especially to the same navy that is wanting him dead because he is a pirate. This simply begs me to write Donal's final letter to Lorelei just so everything will be explained.

  However, I'm still trying to explain why Lorelei would commit to a man twice her age. Of course, some aspects of their relationship has already been discussed between Brittany and I. For example, why would Ben ( A man who likes his women polite, clean, courteous, and in dresses) find an enamoring attraction to Lorelei? Well, she is bascially the embodiment of rebellion according to Ben's social ideas. She is a pirate, a woman who wears breeches and not skirts, and most of all is free. These are all contradictions to Ben. We are all tempted more than once by the dark side, the side that rebels. Thus, Ben's attraction to Lorelei makes a lot of sense. Lorelei is everything dangerous and Ben is attracted to that danger. Lorelei is a much different part of society comparedto what Ben was born and raised with.

  The same idea applies to Lorelei. She was raised around rowdy, disrespectful pirates. So on the occasion she meets Ben she is quite taken with him. He is clean, well educated, well mannered, and extremely respectful to women. Okay, yes, he is bitter towards Lorelei in the beginning because she sunk his ship and pretty much ruined his life, but he was never terrible to her. Therefore, Ben is Lorelei's rebellion against the norms she was raised with. He is naval and she is pirate. That alone makes them a rather daring couple.

  I love Ben and Lorelei. :)

 Plus, I'm glad I'm not the only one who thinks the way I do. :P

Okay, lets face it. I have been on a Master and Commander streak for about a week now. (In case Cion hasn't noticed.) And falling back into this groove has brought back memories of what used to be.

  I remember when I first tumbled into the fandom of tallships and handsome naval officers. I joined an RPG board based off the movie that was moderated by the one and only <lj user=cion>. Since most of the main characters were already taken I created my own character who goes, and still does, by the name of Lorelei. She began as a merchant's daughter who was salvaged from a ship wreck. Her father's ship had been attacked by pirates. For awhile she was the only female character on the board and generated her own share of attention and romances. I was in love. Not with just the movie in itself, but everything. The RPG, the characters, the people behind the characters. Most of all it introduced me to the Age of Sail and tallships.  Sure, even before the movie I had the faint romantic ideals of pirates and sailing, but I didn't know nothing then.
  Unfortunately, the board did fall upon hard times which nearly shattered many of the friendships that had developed. Somehow in that time I became radical and completely remolded Lorelei from a merchant's daughter. The idea was she held a secret that was liable to get her hung. She was a pirate and still is today. 
  Regardless, there were many happy times. I remember when another female character was introduced to the boards who went by the name Gabby. Oh, the fun they had! We plotted (mutiny on the Surprise), we flirted (Gabby eventually got Tom and Lorelei had a fling with Jack XD), and had drunken romps (starfish are so wonderful, a shame we never got to pinch their bums). Hey, Cion, remember when Lorelei forced Jack into wearing a kilt?
   Oh, and I was such a nut at writing short stories and poetry dedicated to our cast and crew. I was actaully looking over them the other day. I read over "Dance Lessons" (the time when Jack and Tom were trying to teach Lorelei how to dance) and it made me smile.
  Anyways, it would  be wrong to say that all good things come to an end. Because in truth it hasn't. Yes, its true the fandom has faded and the RPG board that <lj user=tselmende> runs is no longer as active as it used to be. For a few of us the passion is still there. Plus, I still have two great friendships that have come out of this. (You know who you are. :) ) So, no, not everything comes to an end. There are things that do lie deeper. As I mentioned before is passion. Even though Master and Commander now seems bygone and pirates have taken over, it is still sailing. People are still fascinated by life at sea whether a naval officer dedicated to their country or a pirate who lives by their own rules. The M&C movie opened that door of possibilties to a world many of us did not know. Then POTC helped to widen that vision. 
   And even though Lorelei is a pirate by and by that does not make me personally an enemy to the British Navy. Besides Lorelei should not be looked upon to harshly. The common history among pirates was they NEVER attacked naval vessels because they knew they would easily be outmatched. They only attacked merchant ships. In Lorelei's history she has only attacked two naval ships and that was only because she in turn was being attacked. The first was when her father's ship the Sea Serpent was attacked and Lorelei had command because her father was mysteriously absent. (The naval ship that attacked was later transformed into the Tempest.) The second time she attacked a naval ship was when Ben was given orders to hunt her down and destroy her. (This time she sunk the ship.)
....Woah, I'm rambling.
  I guess to say in conclusion is that all fandoms will come to an end. M&C is passing and eventually it will happen to POTC too. But the impressions they leave us will last forever. I can truly say that if it were not for M&C my fascination with sailing would not be as great. So when I go back to reading the Patrick O'Brian series its because I love the period, the people, the ideas, the courage it took for men to leave their homes and sail on waters unchartered. It took many brave many in the history of the world to give us what we have today. Maybe sometimes we should pause and consider that.
